labels.label: Get csv file with a HTTP request, split csv lines and extract values from the lines by validating them with a regex
With the values extracted as attributes of a flowfile, build a cql INSERT statement in a corresponding table of a tenant. Then, with connected Cassandra cluster insert data into it.

processors.name: SplitText - Get lines of a CSV file

entry.value: insert into data.ddata (time, readable_time, acceleration, acceleration_x, acceleration_y, acceleration_z, battery, humidity, pressure, temperature, dev_id) values ('${column.1}', '${column.2}', ${column.3}, ${column.4}, ${column.5}, ${column.6}, ${column.7}, ${column.8}, ${column.9}, ${column.10}, '${column.12}')
